<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="507" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d507">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 738.3915/113.]</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister to
                                    Haiti</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 6, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>General Zamor at Cape Haitien telegraphs that Dominican troops have again
                            crossed the frontier near Ouanaminthe and are fighting and devastating
                            the country. As this is the second time recently that Dominican troops
                            have invaded Haitian territory, the Haitian Government now contemplates
                            vigorous measures. From the attitude of the Dominican Government as
                            expressed to me by the Dominican Minister it appears that the invasion
                            is intended to bring about a clash between the two countries.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Furniss.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>